To create S3  1.Through Terraform File
=========================================

Now we will do create S3 bucket through Terraform
===================================================

vim provider.tf ------------------------------------------>

provider "aws" {
region = "us-east-2"
}

:wq ------------------------------------------>

vim main.tf ------------------------------------------>

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "mybucket" {
bucket = "bucketname"
}

:wq ------------------------------------------>

as of now bucket will get created 
now we will do enable versioning also after creating bucket also

vim main.tf ------------------------------------------>

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "mybucket" {
bucket = "bucketname"
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_versioning" "bucketversioning" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.mybucket.id
  versioning_configuration {
    status = "Enabled"
  }
}

:wq ------------------------------------------>


terrform init ----------------------------------------->

now if we give terraform plan we will get error is permission denied as IAM permissions previously given for Jenkins not for Terraform 

aws configure ---------------------------------------->

access key: give here access key
secret key: give here secret key
region: give region also here

now give terrafom plan ----------------------------------->

It will work now

terraform apply --aouto-approve ------------------------------->

very very important to know is as of now we know how to store war files in a bucket 
need to know how to store state files is very very important

for suppose if we create anything like created ec2-instance, s3 bucket we will get state files 
now i want to store that state files in this S3 Bucket for that we will write seperate backend file for that

