3. How to make web host through S3
=======================================

we can do static & dynamic web host as well by using S3 for this we need html file

select created S3 bucket------------> and upload html file in it ----------> select properties -------> go to last option ---------> do enable static website 
hosting --------> index document: index.html -------------> save changes

after this one dns name will name will give for that dns name we can access the application easily for suppose if we got any error means we need to give enable ACL 
permission to the bucket & object as well like below

select bucket ------------->properties ----------> select block public access---------> do enabe Access Control List-------> save changes 

now we can able to access the application easily


In additionally another option will have in S3 is CRR (Cross Region Replication) means to do S3 replications from one account to another account

Finally data should need to be done replication bucket to bucket for that we will use CRR (Cross Region Replication)

lets see how pratically is like below

example create 2 buckets 1. is Source bucket & 2. is destination bucket and do enable ACL & versioning as well

Now if any object upload in source bucket that object should need to go in destination bucket same way 
if any object upload in destination bucket that object should need to go in source bucket

for that we will use CRR (Cross Region Replication) need to be enable that

select source bucket----------> select management-----------> create replication rule ------> name: rule1-------> status: enable -------------> select apply 
to all objects in the bucket ---------> destination: bucket name : give here destination bucket name ---------> iAM role: create new role------> save

same process will do in destination bucket as well

select destination bucket----------> select management-----------> create replication rule ------> name: rule1-------> status: enable -------------> select apply 
to all objects in the bucket ---------> destination: bucket name : give here destination bucket name ---------> iAM role: create new role------> save

